{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"80395077-2ddc-4040-9d44-ac818762782f","content":"**Use `dotnet workload update`.**\n\n- **`dotnet workload update`** — downloads and installs the latest versions of all installed workloads to match your current SDK. After an SDK update, this is what brings your MAUI workload back in sync.\n\n- **`dotnet workload repair`** — reinstalls the *same* versions already recorded. It fixes corrupted or incomplete installations but won't pull newer workload packages that the updated SDK requires.\n\n**Quick fix:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\ndotnet build\n```\n\nIf the build still fails after updating, check `dotnet workload list` to confirm `maui` (or `maui-android`, `maui-ios`, etc.) is listed, and reinstall if missing:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload install maui\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dc59bb7b-290d-4487-ab90-fb0e39d2fdeb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI workload management — specifically whether to use `dotnet workload update` or `dotnet workload repair` after a SDK update broke their build. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":258,"requestId":"482C:386B3C:53A770E:5BC68B0:69F3FA44"},"id":"cf899cb8-d3a7-4b39-b1d0-c7e4b93f593f","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:56:44.198Z","parentId":"f1666506-136b-45cd-8033-59aad364c541"}
